The purpose of an evaluation is to determine:</text> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="2" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <spacer width="10" /> </cell> <cell cell-span="10"> <text font-size="medium">- Whether the child has or continues to have one or more disabilities;</text> </cell> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <spacer width="10" /> </cell> <cell cell-span="10"> <text font-size="medium">- The present levels of academic achievement and functional performance of the child;</text> </cell> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <spacer width="10" /> </cell> <cell cell-span="10"> <text font-size="medium">- Whether the disability is adversely affecting the child''s education; and,</text> </cell> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <spacer width="10" /> </cell> <cell cell-span="10"> <text font-size="medium">- Whether the child needs or continues to need special education and related services.</text> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium">As you know, you previously signed consent for the initial evaluation or reevaluation of your child to determine if he or she has or continues to have a disability and is eligible for special education and related services. This evaluation is in process and is being conducted in accordance with the documented decision of the IEP Team, of which you are a member, with regard to the nature and scope of the evaluation. The state special education rules require that within 60 school days from the date of parent/guardian consent, a conference must be held to discuss the evaluation findings and determine eligibility for special education and related services.</text> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium">The federal special education regulations at 34 CFR 300.3009(c) allow the 60 school-day timeline to be extended when conducting an evaluation of a student with or suspected of having a specific learning disability. Such an extension may only occur through mutual written agreement of the child''s parents and a group of qualified professionals (as described in 34 CFR 300.306(a)(1)).</text> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="5" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium" underline="true">We are proposing to extend the evaluation timeline by </text> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-days" label-display="false" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium" underline="true"> school days, which will have the effect of changing the completion date from </text> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-from" label-display="false" /> <text font-size="medium" underline="true"> to </text> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-to" label-display="false" /> </line> <line shaded="true" > <text font-size="medium" underline="true">, for the reason(s) discussed below. This extension cannot have the effect of delaying or denying the provision of a free, appropriate public education for your child.</text> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="1" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium" bold="true">Reason(s) for Timeline Extension:</text> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-reason" rows="2" label-display="false" /> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="10" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium" bold="true">DISTRICT AGREEMENT TO EXTEND THE TIMELINE</text> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium">The school district hereby agrees to extend the evaluation timeline as specified above.</text> </line> <line shaded="true"> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-representative" label="Representative" label-display="right" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <spacer height="10" /> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium" bold="true">PARENT/GUARDIAN ARGEEMENT TO EXTEND THE TIMELINE</text> </line> <line shaded="true"> <text font-size="medium">I understand the school district (group of qualified professionals as described in 34 CFR 300.306(a)(1)) must have my agreement to extend the timeline to complete the evaluation. If I do not agree to extend the evaluation timeline, the district is required to complete the evaluation and determine eligibility within the 60 school day timeline. I understand my rights as explained to me and contained in the Explanation of Procedural Safeguards.</text> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <radio font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-agree" value="-1" bold="true" underline="true">Not chosen</radio> </cell> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <radio font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-agree" value="1" bold="true" underline="true">I agree</radio> </cell> <cell cell-span="10" line-span="2"> <text font-size="medium" bold="true">to extend the 60 school day timeline as specified above to complete the special education evaluation of my child and determine his or her initial or continued eligibility in the category of specific learning disability.</text> </cell> </line> <line shaded="true"> <cell cell-span="1"> <radio font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-agree" value="0" bold="true" underline="true">I do not agree</radio> </cell> </line> <line border="none" shaded="true"> <spacer height="10" /> </line> <line shaded="true"> <property font-size="medium" alias="agr-ext-time-signed-date" label="Signed Date" label-display="right" /> </line> </block> </row> </tab> </template>' WHERE VWT_OID = 'vwtX2IL3457m' AND (VWT_CUSTOM_IND <> '1' OR VWT_CUSTOM_IND IS NULL);
